327
00:25:51,499 --> 00:25:52,932
Where are you going?

328
00:25:53,001 --> 00:25:54,764
To the cell, talk to my client.

329
00:25:54,836 --> 00:25:56,269
What, are you nuts?

330
00:25:56,338 --> 00:25:58,499
l want to speak to him face to face.

331
00:25:59,708 --> 00:26:00,675
Well....

332
00:26:02,911 --> 00:26:05,004
You've already signed the release.

333
00:26:10,619 --> 00:26:11,950
lt's your life.

334
00:26:16,691 --> 00:26:17,658
Hi.

335
00:26:18,860 --> 00:26:20,919
So, then, Mr. Young, is it?

336
00:26:23,198 --> 00:26:25,325
You're Mr. Young, is that correct?

337
00:26:27,202 --> 00:26:29,329
Mr. Young, that is your name, isn't it?

338
00:26:29,437 --> 00:26:30,563
Henri Young?

339
00:26:33,341 --> 00:26:37,209
l'll just assume that's your name
until you tell me differently.

340
00:26:37,612 --> 00:26:40,479
Mr. Young, l will be acting
as your defense attorney.

341
00:26:40,548 --> 00:26:43,108
l'm James Stamphill
and anything you tell me...

342
00:26:43,218 --> 00:26:46,813
...will be protected under the rules
of confidentiality...

343
00:26:46,955 --> 00:26:50,083
...of the attorney-client relationship.
So feel completely free...

344
00:26:50,191 --> 00:26:53,490
...to answer my questions
in an honest and forthright fashion.

345
00:26:53,561 --> 00:26:56,860
Just for the record,
your name is Henri Young, right?

346
00:27:01,169 --> 00:27:04,502
This isn't an admission of guilt.
lt's just your name.

347
00:27:06,374 --> 00:27:07,739
You speak English?

348
00:27:09,644 --> 00:27:13,205
Yeah, you do speak English.
lt says so right here in the file.

349
00:27:19,921 --> 00:27:21,115
Mr. Young...

350
00:27:22,791 --> 00:27:27,490
...l am your attorney but l can't provide you
with much of a defense if one of us is...

351
00:27:27,996 --> 00:27:29,190
...catatonic.

352
00:27:30,098 --> 00:27:31,292
You see...

353
00:27:31,700 --> 00:27:35,659
...we both have to be able and willing
to answer when our name is called.

354
00:27:39,374 --> 00:27:40,841
Can you hear?

355
00:27:58,393 --> 00:27:59,621
Mr. Young?

356
00:28:01,629 --> 00:28:03,153
You okay, Mr. Young?

357
00:28:03,331 --> 00:28:05,993
<i>Henri Young was born in Kansas in 1913.</i>

358
00:28:07,635 --> 00:28:09,967
<i>His parents died ten years later...</i>

359
00:28:10,038 --> 00:28:12,336
<i>...leaving Henri to raise his younger sister.</i>

360
00:28:13,575 --> 00:28:17,272
<i>At the age of 17, Henri went into
a local store to try to get a job.</i>

361
00:28:19,080 --> 00:28:20,843
<i>He was refused work.</i>

362
00:28:22,217 --> 00:28:26,119
<i>Out of desperation he reached
into the cash register and took $5.</i>

363
00:28:27,422 --> 00:28:30,482
<i>The store also doubled
as the town's post office.</i>

364
00:28:31,926 --> 00:28:35,862
<i>Henri was tried and convicted
of the federal crime of mail robbery.</i>

365
00:28:37,499 --> 00:28:40,400
<i>Henri's sister was taken
to live in an orphanage.</i>

366
00:28:42,303 --> 00:28:44,203
<i>He would never see her again.</i>

367
00:28:45,874 --> 00:28:48,809
<i>Eleven years later,
Henri would kill Rufus McCain.</i>

368
00:29:16,037 --> 00:29:17,334
Mr. Young...

369
00:29:17,739 --> 00:29:19,730
...you killed a guy, so...

370
00:29:20,308 --> 00:29:22,208
...you're not catatonic.

371
00:29:24,512 --> 00:29:26,480
l know that you can talk.

372
00:29:27,482 --> 00:29:28,949
l don't know...

373
00:29:29,951 --> 00:29:32,385
...maybe you could write something.

374
00:29:35,023 --> 00:29:37,514
You want to write something? Write here.

375
00:29:40,662 --> 00:29:42,323
Something. Just....

376
00:29:43,398 --> 00:29:45,457
Look, you want to give it a try?

377
00:29:45,633 --> 00:29:47,191
You want to write?

378
00:29:51,739 --> 00:29:53,070
Something...

379
00:29:53,241 --> 00:29:54,469
...please.

380
00:29:56,511 --> 00:29:58,741
Mr. Young, you're looking at me.

381
00:29:59,080 --> 00:30:00,911
You hear me, don't you?

382
00:30:03,418 --> 00:30:07,115
lf you won't answer my questions,
maybe we can start with something else.

383
00:30:07,222 --> 00:30:09,986
What do you want?
There has to be something.

384
00:30:10,058 --> 00:30:14,051
Can't be to sit there, because if you do,
they'll just stick you in the gas chamber.

385
00:30:14,162 --> 00:30:15,789
Do you understand that?

386
00:30:29,110 --> 00:30:30,077
Look...

387
00:30:32,180 --> 00:30:34,273
...Mr. Young, l've read your file.

388
00:30:35,717 --> 00:30:37,708
l am trying to help you.

389
00:30:38,486 --> 00:30:41,455
That's all l'm trying to do.
l just want to help you.

390
00:30:42,123 --> 00:30:43,556
Maybe there are...

391
00:30:44,092 --> 00:30:46,652
...extenuating circumstances in your case.

392
00:30:48,730 --> 00:30:51,460
Getting sentenced to Leavenworth
for stealing...

393
00:30:51,633 --> 00:30:53,601
...$500, that's extenuating.

394
00:30:58,706 --> 00:31:01,266
You have to understand, l'm on your side.

395
00:31:01,576 --> 00:31:02,406
$5.

396
00:31:02,477 --> 00:31:03,808
What, Mr. Young?

397
00:31:05,880 --> 00:31:07,814
lt was $5, not $500.

398
00:31:08,950 --> 00:31:12,818
l knew you had it in you. Now, come on.
Why did you kill Rufus McCain?

399
00:31:13,755 --> 00:31:16,246
You just talked. Don't do this again.

400
00:31:16,958 --> 00:31:20,121
Come on, don't quit now.
Come on, you just talked!

401
00:31:20,662 --> 00:31:22,289
Why did you kill McCain?

402
00:31:28,603 --> 00:31:29,570
What?

403
00:31:30,505 --> 00:31:32,336
-What are you saying?
-How....

404
00:31:32,407 --> 00:31:33,931
How? How? How?

405
00:31:34,742 --> 00:31:36,175
Are you saying ''how''?

406
00:31:36,244 --> 00:31:37,268
How.

407
00:31:37,879 --> 00:31:38,846
How?

408
00:31:39,514 --> 00:31:40,538
How.

409
00:31:42,016 --> 00:31:45,952
How. What are you, a fucking lndian?
