412
00:31:51,025 --> 00:31:52,049
How is....

413
00:31:52,660 --> 00:31:53,456
Who?

414
00:31:53,528 --> 00:31:54,722
DiMaggio.

415
00:31:55,129 --> 00:31:56,687
How is DiMaggio?

416
00:31:57,131 --> 00:31:59,224
ls he a prisoner over at Alcatraz?

417
00:31:59,867 --> 00:32:00,891
How is...

418
00:32:01,135 --> 00:32:02,432
...DiMaggio...

419
00:32:02,637 --> 00:32:04,104
...doing this year?

420
00:32:05,873 --> 00:32:08,103
DiMaggio, the baseball player?

421
00:32:08,643 --> 00:32:09,610
Yeah.

422
00:32:11,145 --> 00:32:15,673
How is Joe DiMaggio, the baseball player,
doing? That's what you're asking?

423
00:32:22,757 --> 00:32:24,156
Mr. Young...

424
00:32:27,729 --> 00:32:29,594
...l don't really follow baseball.

425
00:32:31,065 --> 00:32:32,123
You know.

426
00:32:42,343 --> 00:32:45,005
<i>Excuse me, Mr. McNeil,
I'm James Stamphill.</i>

427
00:32:46,180 --> 00:32:48,148
-Counsel for Henri Young.
-Yes.

428
00:32:48,216 --> 00:32:51,185
l was wondering if l could talk to you
about continuance?

429
00:32:51,252 --> 00:32:52,219
No.

430
00:32:52,320 --> 00:32:55,118
You don't understand.
He just sits there and won't speak.

431
00:32:55,189 --> 00:32:59,148
Maybe he's practicing for the gas chamber.
Tell him to take deep breaths.

432
00:32:59,260 --> 00:33:02,957
You won't even consider a joint motion
in the interest of justice?

433
00:33:03,431 --> 00:33:06,366
-Are you old enough to be a lawyer?
