750
00:50:33,847 --> 00:50:34,871
Thank you.

751
00:50:35,182 --> 00:50:37,377
<i>So many opinions being expressed.</i>

752
00:50:37,584 --> 00:50:40,815
<i>We attempted to get a statement
from the recent Harvard graduate...</i>

753
00:50:40,921 --> 00:50:43,355
<i>...assigned to defend Henri Young.</i>

754
00:50:43,790 --> 00:50:46,953
Why don't we keep the trial
in the courtroom? Thank you.

755
00:50:48,095 --> 00:50:51,724
l would like to address a few words
to the counsel for the defense.

756
00:50:51,865 --> 00:50:54,493
Mr. Stamphill, you are hereby
put on notice...

757
00:50:54,701 --> 00:50:57,670
...that this court has no interest
in newspaper headlines...

758
00:50:57,771 --> 00:50:59,898
...and will not be swayed by them.

759
00:51:00,674 --> 00:51:05,509
l further admonish that counsel's attempts
to try this case in the press...

760
00:51:05,612 --> 00:51:09,378
...and not before this court,
will put him in the utmost peril.

761
00:51:11,551 --> 00:51:13,485
ls that clear, Mr. Stamphill?

762
00:51:13,720 --> 00:51:15,119
Yes, Your Honor.

763
00:51:15,455 --> 00:51:16,513
Good.

764
00:51:17,190 --> 00:51:19,090
Bailiff, approach the bench.

765
00:51:19,559 --> 00:51:23,086
Before l hand down my ruling
on Mr. McNeil's objection...

766
00:51:23,597 --> 00:51:27,192
...l'd like to address a few words
to the counsel for the defense.

767
00:51:27,300 --> 00:51:31,566
While l cannot give legal advice
and sit on the bench at the same time...

768
00:51:31,738 --> 00:51:35,435
...l will express grave concern
with the defense's strategy.

769
00:51:36,409 --> 00:51:39,537
Counselor, l strongly recommend
you walk a straight line...

770
00:51:39,646 --> 00:51:41,375
...in terms of your defense.

771
00:51:41,481 --> 00:51:46,043
Anything you state in this courtroom
will be evaluated not only by the jury...

772
00:51:46,253 --> 00:51:50,451
...but very closely scrutinized by myself.
ls that understood, Mr. Stamphill?

773
00:51:50,991 --> 00:51:52,117
Yes, Your Honor.

774
00:51:52,559 --> 00:51:53,685
Very well.

775
00:51:55,362 --> 00:51:57,421
Prosecution's objection is overruled.

776
00:51:58,331 --> 00:52:00,925
You may pursue your line of defense...

777
00:52:01,168 --> 00:52:03,432
...concerning the penitentiary at Alcatraz...

778
00:52:03,503 --> 00:52:07,064
...and l will rule on any objections
on a point-by-point basis.

779
00:52:07,274 --> 00:52:08,468
Exception.

780
00:52:08,642 --> 00:52:09,666
Noted.

781
00:52:09,776 --> 00:52:12,301
Mr. McNeil, you may call
your first witness.

782
00:52:12,512 --> 00:52:14,980
Prosecution calls Terrence Swenson.

783
00:52:16,449 --> 00:52:17,780
Terrence Swenson.

784
00:52:26,893 --> 00:52:29,862
Witness shall remain standing
until sworn in.

785
00:52:31,198 --> 00:52:32,927
Put your hand on the Bible.

786
00:52:33,033 --> 00:52:34,261
Cut it out.

787
00:52:34,367 --> 00:52:37,336
Do you swear to tell the truth
and nothing but the truth...

788
00:52:37,804 --> 00:52:39,294
...so help you God?

789
00:52:39,439 --> 00:52:40,770
So help me God.

790
00:52:40,874 --> 00:52:42,307
You may be seated.

791
00:52:43,310 --> 00:52:47,474
Mr. Swenson, as a guard at Alcatraz,
did you know Henri Young?

792
00:52:48,048 --> 00:52:48,776
Yes, sir.

793
00:52:48,882 --> 00:52:51,180
Could you point him out for us?

794
00:52:52,385 --> 00:52:54,444
That's him right over there, sir.

795
00:52:54,955 --> 00:52:56,582
Thank you, Mr. Whitney.

796
00:52:57,224 --> 00:52:58,122
Thank you.

797
00:52:58,191 --> 00:53:01,524
Now, on the morning of June 1 1, 1941,
where were you?

798
00:53:02,162 --> 00:53:04,562
l was on duty in the dining hall.

799
00:53:04,898 --> 00:53:06,456
Everything was normal.

800
00:53:06,833 --> 00:53:08,767
And l saw the defendant--

801
00:53:08,902 --> 00:53:09,960
Henri Young.

802
00:53:10,070 --> 00:53:11,401
That's correct.

803
00:53:11,738 --> 00:53:13,968
l saw him standing over Rufus McCain.

804
00:53:14,241 --> 00:53:16,300
He lifted up his chin and....

805
00:53:16,943 --> 00:53:19,002
-Excuse me, l'm nervous.
-lt's all right.

806
00:53:19,079 --> 00:53:21,570
And he plunged a metal object...

807
00:53:22,515 --> 00:53:24,642
...which l later learned was a spoon...

808
00:53:24,751 --> 00:53:26,412
...into McCain's throat.

809
00:53:27,187 --> 00:53:28,984
He then ripped it open.

810
00:53:30,423 --> 00:53:32,857
Did the defendant ever appear
to be ranting...

811
00:53:32,926 --> 00:53:33,893
...or raving?

812
00:53:33,994 --> 00:53:35,120
No, sir.

813
00:53:35,295 --> 00:53:37,820
Mr. McKeon, was he frothing
at the mouth?

814
00:53:38,164 --> 00:53:39,096
No, sir.

815
00:53:39,699 --> 00:53:43,157
Did he in any way give the impression
of one who was insane?

816
00:53:43,436 --> 00:53:46,564
Objection. This man is not
a qualified psychiatrist.

817
00:53:46,673 --> 00:53:47,731
Sustained.

818
00:53:47,941 --> 00:53:51,900
So, it appeared to you that it was a cool,
calculated and deliberate act?

819
00:53:52,279 --> 00:53:54,008
-Objection!
-Overruled.

820
00:53:54,214 --> 00:53:56,580
The witness may answer the question.

821
00:53:56,683 --> 00:53:59,811
Yes, sir. Young did it,
just as cool as a cucumber.

822
00:54:00,086 --> 00:54:01,212
Thank you.

823
00:54:01,488 --> 00:54:02,853
No further questions.

824
00:54:03,290 --> 00:54:06,259
This court will reconvene
after the holiday...

825
00:54:06,326 --> 00:54:07,953
...9:00 a.m., July 5.

826
00:54:08,128 --> 00:54:09,220
All rise.

827
00:54:09,329 --> 00:54:11,661
You should have played cards with me.

828
00:54:12,232 --> 00:54:13,460
Alcatraz.

829
00:54:13,967 --> 00:54:16,936
lt was built by the military
during the Civil War.

830
00:54:18,071 --> 00:54:21,472
ln May of '33, the War Department
abandoned the island.

831
00:54:22,475 --> 00:54:26,741
lt was leveled, all except for the lower
floor which is now used for storage.

832
00:54:27,080 --> 00:54:30,140
Note to myself:
Get access to the lower level...

833
00:54:30,283 --> 00:54:33,514
...because that's where the dungeons have
gotta be located.

834
00:54:33,653 --> 00:54:36,281
The only guard on record to be fired...

835
00:54:36,389 --> 00:54:40,018
...or dismissed during Henri's solitary time
was Derek Simpson.

836
00:54:40,560 --> 00:54:42,050
Locate Simpson.

837
00:54:42,329 --> 00:54:45,696
The prison opened in June of '34
under Warden Humson.

838
00:54:46,599 --> 00:54:49,534
He insisted on a high level
of guards to prisoners.

839
00:54:49,602 --> 00:54:51,570
Glenn was the first appointee.

840
00:54:53,340 --> 00:54:54,466
Mr. Henkin.

841
00:54:54,774 --> 00:54:57,265
Two things: First of all, you work for me.

842
00:54:57,444 --> 00:54:58,911
Let me finish!

843
00:55:00,013 --> 00:55:03,574
You work for me, which means
when l call you, you drop everything.

844
00:55:03,683 --> 00:55:06,379
Return my call or you will cease
to work for me.

845
00:55:06,686 --> 00:55:08,984
l don't care if you're with Rita Hayworth!

846
00:55:09,356 --> 00:55:10,448
Understand?

847
00:55:10,757 --> 00:55:12,190
-Yes, sir.
-Good.

848
00:55:15,295 --> 00:55:17,627
What the hell are you doing with this trial?

849
00:55:17,697 --> 00:55:18,925
Defending my client.

850
00:55:19,032 --> 00:55:21,557
Then why don't you defend him
for Christ's sake?

851
00:55:21,668 --> 00:55:24,899
Try to knock down the charges
as a crime of passion or figure out...

852
00:55:25,005 --> 00:55:27,473
...how you'll cross-examine
the witnesses...

853
00:55:27,540 --> 00:55:32,170
...instead of this ''psychological coma'' crap
that doesn't mean anything in court!

854
00:55:32,379 --> 00:55:34,540
l think it does. As long as it's my case--

855
00:55:34,647 --> 00:55:39,107
Fair enough. l tried to talk reasonably
to you, but you're not going for it, so...

856
00:55:39,819 --> 00:55:42,788
...you're not handling this case anymore.
lt's done.

857
00:55:42,989 --> 00:55:44,320
Mr. Henkin...

858
00:55:45,225 --> 00:55:48,956
...they're printing my opening statement
in 250 newspapers across the country.

859
00:55:49,062 --> 00:55:52,498
lf you want me off the case because
you're afraid of taking on Alcatraz...

860
00:55:52,599 --> 00:55:54,157
...that's your choice.

861
00:55:54,234 --> 00:55:57,795
But l'll just go to Jerry Hoolihan
and tell my side of the story.

862
00:55:58,405 --> 00:56:01,966
lf you want to play hardball, sir,
l'll play hardball too.

863
00:56:07,914 --> 00:56:09,609
l'm trying to be your friend.

864
00:56:10,417 --> 00:56:12,408
You know who the warden of Alcatraz is?

865
00:56:12,519 --> 00:56:16,853
He's the most highly respected warden
in the US dealing with hardened criminals.

866
00:56:17,857 --> 00:56:20,485
lf you try to make Humson
look like a Nazi...

867
00:56:21,027 --> 00:56:23,222
...they will eat you for breakfast.

868
00:56:32,205 --> 00:56:35,663
You'll die if l can't get corroboration
about what goes on over there.

869
00:56:35,775 --> 00:56:38,744
l need names! Names of men
who'll come and testify.

870
00:56:39,145 --> 00:56:42,273
What made you think
these men will come and testify?

871
00:56:42,382 --> 00:56:45,078
Maybe you got some friends
you don't know about.

872
00:56:45,785 --> 00:56:49,221
-You want to play cards?
-l'll make them testify with a court order!

873
00:56:49,289 --> 00:56:52,383
What about when they're back
on the Rock with Mr. Glenn?

874
00:56:52,525 --> 00:56:54,390
They'll kill them, that's what.

875
00:56:54,461 --> 00:56:57,487
This is our only chance.
We're talking about your life.

876
00:56:57,630 --> 00:57:01,566
For a smart guy, you're awfully slow.
l'm already dead. l told you that.

877
00:57:01,801 --> 00:57:04,065
You can't change Alcatraz.

878
00:57:04,471 --> 00:57:05,631
lt just is.

879
00:57:05,738 --> 00:57:07,103
So why fight it?

880
00:57:07,240 --> 00:57:11,267
You stand in court preaching. l don't
even know what you're talking about.

881
00:57:11,444 --> 00:57:13,639
Justice. l'm talking about justice.

882
00:57:13,980 --> 00:57:16,847
l killed him, they saw it,
they're going to kill me.

883
00:57:16,916 --> 00:57:18,781
Nothing you say will change that.

884
00:57:18,852 --> 00:57:21,343
So l don't see what you're
so excited about.

885
00:57:21,654 --> 00:57:25,488
This trial doesn't interest you at all?
You don't care about it a bit?

886
00:57:26,593 --> 00:57:29,619
You look like you're having
a good time, so....

887
00:57:30,330 --> 00:57:31,922
No, l don't care.

888
00:57:32,332 --> 00:57:36,359
Main thing is, l got a friend my age
to talk to until they gas me.

889
00:57:37,170 --> 00:57:41,630
l'm not your friend, l'm your attorney.
l'm trying to save your life. Guard!

890
00:57:41,941 --> 00:57:44,341
You know, l have a sister, but...

891
00:57:45,345 --> 00:57:47,870
...l ain't seen her since they put me in jail.

892
00:57:47,981 --> 00:57:50,142
l got nothing. l got nobody.

893
00:57:50,350 --> 00:57:53,012
l don't need a lawyer. l need a friend.

894
00:57:53,686 --> 00:57:58,214
You're doing all this to prove something
to a guy named Darryl, not for me.

895
00:57:58,858 --> 00:58:00,985
You want to do something for me?

896
00:58:01,861 --> 00:58:03,453
Let's play cards.

897
00:58:06,366 --> 00:58:08,732
Go ahead and play cards.
l got a case to try.

898
00:58:08,801 --> 00:58:11,269
Hold it, Jim. Where are you going?

899
00:58:11,971 --> 00:58:13,495
Where are you going?

900
00:58:23,116 --> 00:58:26,176
<i>I'm Henri Young's attorney.
I'd like to ask you a few questions.</i>

901
00:58:26,386 --> 00:58:30,117
<i>I'm going to call prisoners to the stand
to testify about life on Alcatraz.</i>

902
00:58:30,223 --> 00:58:31,952
<i>Where are the dungeons?</i>

903
00:58:32,058 --> 00:58:34,288
<i>What is solitary time
in those dungeons like?</i>

904
00:58:34,394 --> 00:58:36,555
<i>I want the jury to know and understand.</i>

905
00:58:36,663 --> 00:58:39,632
<i>You tell them to get caught
robbing a bank. They'll find out.</i>

906
00:58:40,500 --> 00:58:42,092
l'm done talking.

907
00:58:56,749 --> 00:58:57,807
Mr. Murphy...

908
00:58:57,917 --> 00:59:02,377
...if we can get decent treatment for you,
it makes it possible for everyone.

909
00:59:02,589 --> 00:59:07,049
lf we ignore cruelty in one place,
it makes it more acceptable everywhere.

910
00:59:07,360 --> 00:59:09,260
l ain't gonna do shit for you.

911
00:59:09,929 --> 00:59:12,693
You can't get me no good time
knocked off.

912
00:59:12,932 --> 00:59:14,797
You can't get me no privileges.

913
00:59:14,867 --> 00:59:18,826
You can't even get me seconds at dessert.
lf l testify for anybody...

914
00:59:19,038 --> 00:59:22,166
...l testify for the DA.
He's got some juice here.

915
00:59:26,646 --> 00:59:30,047
<i>Mr. Baker, could you tell me anything
about Henri Young?</i>

916
00:59:30,283 --> 00:59:31,910
Don't know Henri Young.

917
00:59:33,052 --> 00:59:35,520
Could you tell us anything
about Mr. Glenn?

918
00:59:37,890 --> 00:59:39,881
Warden Glenn has always been
good to me.

919
00:59:42,962 --> 00:59:45,192
Have you ever been in the dungeons?

920
00:59:45,732 --> 00:59:48,132
l don't know nothing about no dungeons.

921
00:59:48,801 --> 00:59:50,234
That's all, ma'am.

922
00:59:50,637 --> 00:59:52,104
l gotta go now.

923
00:59:56,242 --> 00:59:57,470
Fuck you.

924
00:59:58,144 --> 01:00:01,045
Did Mr. Glenn tell you
not to cooperate with me?

925
01:00:01,547 --> 01:00:02,775
Fuck you.

926
01:00:02,982 --> 01:00:05,246
Where are the dungeons located?

927
01:00:05,618 --> 01:00:07,813
Don't take my fucking picture!

928
01:00:12,191 --> 01:00:15,024
You know l can get
a writ of habeas corpus testificandum...

929
01:00:15,094 --> 01:00:17,688
...and force you to come
and testify in court?

930
01:00:17,830 --> 01:00:19,058
Fuck you!

931
01:00:20,566 --> 01:00:22,761
Thank you very much for your time.

932
01:00:22,869 --> 01:00:24,427
Don't mention it.

933
01:00:26,239 --> 01:00:28,036
And you, sweetheart....

934
01:00:28,508 --> 01:00:30,237
l'd like to fuck you.

935
01:00:47,093 --> 01:00:49,527
<i>I hope your day has been fruitful.</i>

936
01:00:50,997 --> 01:00:54,660
l don't see your photographer.
ls he still taking pictures?

937
01:00:54,867 --> 01:00:56,357
He's trying to.

938
01:00:56,936 --> 01:00:59,461
We're not receiving a great deal
of cooperation.

939
01:00:59,539 --> 01:01:03,202
lt almost seems as though someone told
the prisoners not to talk to us.

940
01:01:03,309 --> 01:01:04,867
There's no conspiracy.

941
01:01:05,211 --> 01:01:06,678
No one talked to them.

942
01:01:06,779 --> 01:01:09,907
Maybe it's because they are
dangerous people who belong here...

943
01:01:10,016 --> 01:01:12,041
...with no interest in you or your case.

944
01:01:12,151 --> 01:01:15,279
-l'd like to see the dungeons.
-l'm sorry? Dungeons?

945
01:01:15,955 --> 01:01:18,219
The old citadel, the sub-level of the prison.

946
01:01:18,324 --> 01:01:20,189
That's mostly storage...

947
01:01:20,259 --> 01:01:22,124
...a few solitary cells.

948
01:01:22,195 --> 01:01:23,093
No dungeons.

949
01:01:23,162 --> 01:01:26,393
l would like to see
the solitary-confinement cells.

950
01:01:26,566 --> 01:01:29,091
l would love to show those cells to you,
but l can't.

951
01:01:29,202 --> 01:01:33,696
lt's an insurance risk to visitors during a
riot. lf you're there, we can't protect you.

952
01:01:33,806 --> 01:01:35,535
Thank you for your concern.

953
01:01:35,975 --> 01:01:38,273
l could show you the exercise yard.

954
01:01:40,413 --> 01:01:41,778
You have papers.

955
01:01:42,215 --> 01:01:45,116
l have papers, so you can cut
the good-guy act.

956
01:01:46,486 --> 01:01:49,182
l do consider myself
as one of the good guys...

957
01:01:49,322 --> 01:01:51,517
...and perhaps more than you...

958
01:01:51,791 --> 01:01:53,850
...l know what the bad guys are like.

959
01:01:53,960 --> 01:01:56,019
l'd like to read them. Please.

960
01:01:57,330 --> 01:01:58,456
Thank you.

961
01:02:00,466 --> 01:02:01,797
That's a court order...

962
01:02:01,868 --> 01:02:05,429
<i>...instructing you to permit us access
to the solitary-confinement cells.</i>

963
01:02:05,538 --> 01:02:08,598
<i>And to allow the photographer
to take pictures of the same...</i>

964
01:02:08,708 --> 01:02:11,734
<i>...to be used as exhibits in the trial
of The People vs. Young.</i>

965
01:02:11,844 --> 01:02:14,074
<i>You are also instructed
to hand over to us...</i>

966
01:02:14,180 --> 01:02:17,707
<i>...the complete medical
and disciplinary files as to therein.</i>

967
01:02:18,017 --> 01:02:19,712
<i>If you refuse to do so...</i>

968
01:02:19,819 --> 01:02:22,879
<i>...you'll have to appear in court
and show just cause.</i>

969
01:02:29,595 --> 01:02:32,155
Why don't you take Miss McCasslin
out for some air?

970
01:02:32,265 --> 01:02:34,062
l was told not to leave you alone.

971
01:02:34,167 --> 01:02:38,331
l don't care. You may be used to
these conditions but obviously she's not.

972
01:02:39,272 --> 01:02:43,732
We've been searched. Take her outside,
or we'll discuss this with Mr. Glenn.

973
01:02:43,843 --> 01:02:45,174
All right.

974
01:02:45,411 --> 01:02:46,742
No more photos.

975
01:02:47,880 --> 01:02:49,108
You all right?

976
01:02:49,615 --> 01:02:50,604
Thanks.

977
01:02:50,817 --> 01:02:52,444
l just need some air.

978
01:03:15,641 --> 01:03:16,801
My God!

979
01:03:38,130 --> 01:03:41,497
My name's James Stamphill.
l'm Henri Young's attorney.

980
01:03:41,567 --> 01:03:44,127
l can force them to let you out
so you can testify...

981
01:03:44,237 --> 01:03:46,205
<i>...in San Francisco in a court of law.</i>

982
01:03:46,272 --> 01:03:50,333
<i>You just have to give me your name.
I promise I will do what I said for you.</i>

983
01:04:05,124 --> 01:04:07,592
James, she's okay. Just needed some air.

984
01:04:11,464 --> 01:04:12,522
Can we go now?

985
01:04:12,632 --> 01:04:14,099
Feeling any better?

986
01:04:15,468 --> 01:04:17,163
l guess l'll make it.

